35static const char *trustnames[] = {
36 "none",
37 "pending-additional",
38 "pending-answer",
39 "additional",
40 "glue",
41 "answer",
42 "authauthority",
43 "authanswer",
44 "secure",
45 "local" /* aka ultimate */
46};
47
48const char *
49dns_trust_totext(dns_trust_t trust) {
50 if (trust >= sizeof(trustnames)/sizeof(*trustnames))
51 return ("bad");
52 return (trustnames[trust]);
53}
54
55#define DNS_RDATASET_COUNT_UNDEFINED UINT32_MAX
56
57void
58dns_rdataset_init(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset) {
59
60 /*
61 * Make 'rdataset' a valid, disassociated rdataset.
62 */
63
64 REQUIRE(rdataset != NULL);
65
66 rdataset->magic = DNS_RDATASET_MAGIC;
67 rdataset->methods = NULL;
68 ISC_LINK_INIT(rdataset, link);
69 rdataset->rdclass = 0;
70 rdataset->type = 0;
71 rdataset->ttl = 0;
72 rdataset->trust = 0;
73 rdataset->covers = 0;
74 rdataset->attributes = 0;
75 rdataset->count = DNS_RDATASET_COUNT_UNDEFINED;
76 rdataset->private1 = NULL;
77 rdataset->private2 = NULL;
78 rdataset->private3 = NULL;
79 rdataset->privateuint4 = 0;
80 rdataset->private5 = NULL;
81 rdataset->private6 = NULL;
82 rdataset->private7 = NULL;
83 rdataset->resign = 0;
84}
85
86void
87dns_rdataset_invalidate(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset) {
88
89 /*
90 * Invalidate 'rdataset'.
91 */
92
93 REQUIRE(DNS_RDATASET_VALID(rdataset));
94 REQUIRE(rdataset->methods == NULL);
95
96 rdataset->magic = 0;
97 ISC_LINK_INIT(rdataset, link);
98 rdataset->rdclass = 0;
99 rdataset->type = 0;
100 rdataset->ttl = 0;
101 rdataset->trust = 0;
102 rdataset->covers = 0;
103 rdataset->attributes = 0;
104 rdataset->count = DNS_RDATASET_COUNT_UNDEFINED;
105 rdataset->private1 = NULL;
106 rdataset->private2 = NULL;
107 rdataset->private3 = NULL;
108 rdataset->privateuint4 = 0;
109 rdataset->private5 = NULL;
110}

112void
113dns_rdataset_disassociate(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset) {
114
115 /*
116 * Disassociate 'rdataset' from its rdata, allowing it to be reused.
117 */
118
119 REQUIRE(DNS_RDATASET_VALID(rdataset));
120 REQUIRE(rdataset->methods != NULL);
121
122 (rdataset->methods->disassociate)(rdataset);
123 rdataset->methods = NULL;
124 ISC_LINK_INIT(rdataset, link);
125 rdataset->rdclass = 0;
126 rdataset->type = 0;
127 rdataset->ttl = 0;
128 rdataset->trust = 0;
129 rdataset->covers = 0;
130 rdataset->attributes = 0;
131 rdataset->count = DNS_RDATASET_COUNT_UNDEFINED;
132 rdataset->private1 = NULL;
133 rdataset->private2 = NULL;
134 rdataset->private3 = NULL;
135 rdataset->privateuint4 = 0;
136 rdataset->private5 = NULL;
137 rdataset->private6 = NULL;
138}

140bool
141dns_rdataset_isassociated(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset) {
142 /*
143 * Is 'rdataset' associated?
144 */
145
146 REQUIRE(DNS_RDATASET_VALID(rdataset));
147
148 if (rdataset->methods != NULL)
149 return (true);
150
151 return (false);
152}

212void
213dns_rdataset_makequestion(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_rdataclass_t rdclass,
214 dns_rdatatype_t type)
215{
216
217 /*
218 * Make 'rdataset' a valid, associated, question rdataset, with a
219 * question class of 'rdclass' and type 'type'.
220 */
221
222 REQUIRE(DNS_RDATASET_VALID(rdataset));
223 REQUIRE(rdataset->methods == NULL);
224
225 rdataset->methods = &question_methods;
226 rdataset->rdclass = rdclass;
227 rdataset->type = type;
228 rdataset->attributes |= DNS_RDATASETATTR_QUESTION;
229}
230
231unsigned int
232dns_rdataset_count(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset) {
233
234 /*
235 * Return the number of records in 'rdataset'.
236 */
237
238 REQUIRE(DNS_RDATASET_VALID(rdataset));
239 REQUIRE(rdataset->methods != NULL);
240
241 return ((rdataset->methods->count)(rdataset));
242}
243
244void
245dns_rdataset_clone(dns_rdataset_t *source, dns_rdataset_t *target) {
246
247 /*
248 * Make 'target' refer to the same rdataset as 'source'.
249 */
250
251 REQUIRE(DNS_RDATASET_VALID(source));
252 REQUIRE(source->methods != NULL);
253 REQUIRE(DNS_RDATASET_VALID(target));
254 REQUIRE(target->methods == NULL);
255
256 (source->methods->clone)(source, target);
257}

260dns_rdataset_first(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset) {
261
262 /*
263 * Move the rdata cursor to the first rdata in the rdataset (if any).
264 */
265
266 REQUIRE(DNS_RDATASET_VALID(rdataset));
267 REQUIRE(rdataset->methods != NULL);
268
269 return ((rdataset->methods->first)(rdataset));
270}

274
275 /*

278
279 REQUIRE(DNS_RDATASET_VALID(rdataset));
280 REQUIRE(rdataset->methods != NULL);
281
282 return ((rdataset->methods->next)(rdataset));

298#define MAX_SHUFFLE 32
299#define WANT_FIXED(r) (((r)->attributes & DNS_RDATASETATTR_FIXEDORDER) != 0)
300#define WANT_RANDOM(r) (((r)->attributes & DNS_RDATASETATTR_RANDOMIZE) != 0)
301#define WANT_CYCLIC(r) (((r)->attributes & DNS_RDATASETATTR_CYCLIC) != 0)
302
303struct towire_sort {
304 int key;
305 dns_rdata_t *rdata;
306};
307
308static int
309towire_compare(const void *av, const void *bv) {
310 const struct towire_sort *a = (const struct towire_sort *) av;
311 const struct towire_sort *b = (const struct towire_sort *) bv;
312 return (a->key - b->key);
313}
314
315static inline void
316swap_rdata(dns_rdata_t *in, unsigned int a, unsigned int b) {
317 dns_rdata_t rdata = in[a];
318 in[a] = in[b];
319 in[b] = rdata;
320}
321
322static isc_result_t
323towiresorted(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, const dns_name_t *owner_name,
324 dns_compress_t *cctx, isc_buffer_t *target,
325 dns_rdatasetorderfunc_t order, const void *order_arg,
326 bool partial, unsigned int options,
327 unsigned int *countp, void **state)
328{
329 isc_region_t r;
330 isc_result_t result;
331 unsigned int i, count = 0, added;
332 isc_buffer_t savedbuffer, rdlen, rrbuffer;
333 unsigned int headlen;
334 bool question = false;
335 bool shuffle = false, sort = false;
336 bool want_random, want_cyclic;
337 dns_rdata_t in_fixed[MAX_SHUFFLE];
338 dns_rdata_t *in = in_fixed;
339 struct towire_sort out_fixed[MAX_SHUFFLE];
340 struct towire_sort *out = out_fixed;
341 dns_fixedname_t fixed;
342 dns_name_t *name;
343 uint16_t offset;
344
345 UNUSED(state);
346
347 /*
348 * Convert 'rdataset' to wire format, compressing names as specified
349 * in cctx, and storing the result in 'target'.
350 */
351
352 REQUIRE(DNS_RDATASET_VALID(rdataset));
353 REQUIRE(rdataset->methods != NULL);
354 REQUIRE(countp != NULL);
355 REQUIRE(cctx != NULL && cctx->mctx != NULL);
356
357 want_random = WANT_RANDOM(rdataset);
358 want_cyclic = WANT_CYCLIC(rdataset);
359
360 if ((rdataset->attributes & DNS_RDATASETATTR_QUESTION) != 0) {
361 question = true;
362 count = 1;
363 result = dns_rdataset_first(rdataset);
364 INSIST(result == ISC_R_NOMORE);
365 } else if ((rdataset->attributes & DNS_RDATASETATTR_NEGATIVE) != 0) {
366 /*
367 * This is a negative caching rdataset.
368 */
369 unsigned int ncache_opts = 0;
370 if ((options & DNS_RDATASETTOWIRE_OMITDNSSEC) != 0)
371 ncache_opts |= DNS_NCACHETOWIRE_OMITDNSSEC;
372 return (dns_ncache_towire(rdataset, cctx, target, ncache_opts,
373 countp));
374 } else {
375 count = (rdataset->methods->count)(rdataset);
376 result = dns_rdataset_first(rdataset);
377 if (result == ISC_R_NOMORE)
378 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
379 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
380 return (result);
381 }
382
383 /*
384 * Do we want to sort and/or shuffle this answer?
385 */
386 if (!question && count > 1 && rdataset->type != dns_rdatatype_rrsig) {
387 if (order != NULL) {
388 sort = true;
389 }
390 if (want_random || want_cyclic) {
391 shuffle = true;
392 }
393 }
394
395 if ((shuffle || sort)) {
396 if (count > MAX_SHUFFLE) {
397 in = isc_mem_get(cctx->mctx, count * sizeof(*in));
398 out = isc_mem_get(cctx->mctx, count * sizeof(*out));
399 if (in == NULL || out == NULL) {
400 shuffle = sort = false;
401 }
402 }
403 }
404
405 if ((shuffle || sort)) {
406 uint32_t seed = 0;
407 unsigned int j = 0;
408
409 /*
410 * First we get handles to all of the rdata.
411 */
412 i = 0;
413 do {
414 INSIST(i < count);
415 dns_rdata_init(&in[i]);
416 dns_rdataset_current(rdataset, &in[i]);
417 i++;
418 result = dns_rdataset_next(rdataset);
419 } while (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
420 if (result != ISC_R_NOMORE) {
421 goto cleanup;
422 }
423 INSIST(i == count);
424
425 if (ISC_LIKELY(want_random)) {
426 seed = isc_random32();
427 }
428
429 if (ISC_UNLIKELY(want_cyclic) &&
430 (rdataset->count != DNS_RDATASET_COUNT_UNDEFINED))
431 {
432 j = rdataset->count % count;
433 }
434
435 for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
436 if (ISC_LIKELY(want_random)) {
437 swap_rdata(in, j, j + seed % (count - j));
438 }
439
440 out[i].key = (sort) ?
441 (*order)(&in[j], order_arg) :
442 0;
443 out[i].rdata = &in[j];
444 if (++j == count) {
445 j = 0;
446 }
447 }
448 /*
449 * Sortlist order.
450 */
451 if (sort) {
452 qsort(out, count, sizeof(out[0]), towire_compare);
453 }
454 }
455
456 savedbuffer = *target;
457 i = 0;
458 added = 0;
459
460 name = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixed);
461 dns_name_copy(owner_name, name, NULL);
462 dns_rdataset_getownercase(rdataset, name);
463 offset = 0xffff;
464
465 name->attributes |= owner_name->attributes &
466 DNS_NAMEATTR_NOCOMPRESS;
467
468 do {
469 /*
470 * Copy out the name, type, class, ttl.
471 */
472
473 rrbuffer = *target;
474 dns_compress_setmethods(cctx, DNS_COMPRESS_GLOBAL14);
475 result = dns_name_towire2(name, cctx, target, &offset);
476 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
477 goto rollback;
478 headlen = sizeof(dns_rdataclass_t) + sizeof(dns_rdatatype_t);
479 if (!question)
480 headlen += sizeof(dns_ttl_t)
481 + 2; /* XXX 2 for rdata len */
482 isc_buffer_availableregion(target, &r);
483 if (r.length < headlen) {
484 result = ISC_R_NOSPACE;
485 goto rollback;
486 }
487 isc_buffer_putuint16(target, rdataset->type);
488 isc_buffer_putuint16(target, rdataset->rdclass);
489 if (!question) {
490 dns_rdata_t rdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
491
492 isc_buffer_putuint32(target, rdataset->ttl);
493
494 /*
495 * Save space for rdlen.
496 */
497 rdlen = *target;
498 isc_buffer_add(target, 2);
499
500 /*
501 * Copy out the rdata
502 */
503 if (shuffle || sort) {
504 rdata = *(out[i].rdata);
505 } else {
506 dns_rdata_reset(&rdata);
507 dns_rdataset_current(rdataset, &rdata);
508 }
509 result = dns_rdata_towire(&rdata, cctx, target);
510 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
511 goto rollback;
512 INSIST((target->used >= rdlen.used + 2) &&
513 (target->used - rdlen.used - 2 < 65536));
514 isc_buffer_putuint16(&rdlen,
515 (uint16_t)(target->used -
516 rdlen.used - 2));
517 added++;
518 }
519
520 if (shuffle || sort) {
521 i++;
522 if (i == count)
523 result = ISC_R_NOMORE;
524 else
525 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
526 } else {
527 result = dns_rdataset_next(rdataset);
528 }
529 } while (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
530
531 if (result != ISC_R_NOMORE)
532 goto rollback;
533
534 *countp += count;
535
536 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
537 goto cleanup;
538
539 rollback:
540 if (partial && result == ISC_R_NOSPACE) {
541 INSIST(rrbuffer.used < 65536);
542 dns_compress_rollback(cctx, (uint16_t)rrbuffer.used);
543 *countp += added;
544 *target = rrbuffer;
545 goto cleanup;
546 }
547 INSIST(savedbuffer.used < 65536);
548 dns_compress_rollback(cctx, (uint16_t)savedbuffer.used);
549 *countp = 0;
550 *target = savedbuffer;
551
552 cleanup:
553 if (out != NULL && out != out_fixed)
554 isc_mem_put(cctx->mctx, out, count * sizeof(*out));
555 if (in != NULL && in != in_fixed)
556 isc_mem_put(cctx->mctx, in, count * sizeof(*in));
557 return (result);
558}

561dns_rdataset_towiresorted(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
562 const dns_name_t *owner_name,
563 dns_compress_t *cctx,
564 isc_buffer_t *target,
565 dns_rdatasetorderfunc_t order,
566 const void *order_arg,
567 unsigned int options,
568 unsigned int *countp)
569{
570 return (towiresorted(rdataset, owner_name, cctx, target,
571 order, order_arg, false, options,
572 countp, NULL));
573}

604isc_result_t
605dns_rdataset_additionaldata(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
606 dns_additionaldatafunc_t add, void *arg)
607{
608 dns_rdata_t rdata = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
609 isc_result_t result;
610
611 /*
612 * For each rdata in rdataset, call 'add' for each name and type in the
613 * rdata which is subject to additional section processing.
614 */
615
616 REQUIRE(DNS_RDATASET_VALID(rdataset));
617 REQUIRE((rdataset->attributes & DNS_RDATASETATTR_QUESTION) == 0);
618
619 result = dns_rdataset_first(rdataset);
620 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
621 return (result);
622
623 do {
624 dns_rdataset_current(rdataset, &rdata);
625 result = dns_rdata_additionaldata(&rdata, add, arg);
626 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
627 result = dns_rdataset_next(rdataset);
628 dns_rdata_reset(&rdata);
629 } while (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
630
631 if (result != ISC_R_NOMORE)
632 return (result);
633
634 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
635}

728void
729dns_rdataset_trimttl(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_rdataset_t *sigrdataset,
730 dns_rdata_rrsig_t *rrsig, isc_stdtime_t now,
731 bool acceptexpired)
732{
733 uint32_t ttl = 0;
734
735 REQUIRE(DNS_RDATASET_VALID(rdataset));
736 REQUIRE(DNS_RDATASET_VALID(sigrdataset));
737 REQUIRE(rrsig != NULL);
738
739 /*
740 * If we accept expired RRsets keep them for no more than 120 seconds.
741 */
742 if (acceptexpired &&
743 (isc_serial_le(rrsig->timeexpire, ((now + 120) & 0xffffffff)) ||
744 isc_serial_le(rrsig->timeexpire, now)))
745 ttl = 120;
746 else if (isc_serial_ge(rrsig->timeexpire, now))
747 ttl = rrsig->timeexpire - now;
748
749 ttl = ISC_MIN(ISC_MIN(rdataset->ttl, sigrdataset->ttl),
750 ISC_MIN(rrsig->originalttl, ttl));
751 rdataset->ttl = ttl;
752 sigrdataset->ttl = ttl;
753}
754
755isc_result_t
756dns_rdataset_addglue(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_dbversion_t *version,
757 dns_message_t *msg)
758{
759 REQUIRE(DNS_RDATASET_VALID(rdataset));
760 REQUIRE(rdataset->methods != NULL);
761 REQUIRE(rdataset->type == dns_rdatatype_ns);
762
763 if (rdataset->methods->addglue == NULL)
764 return (ISC_R_NOTIMPLEMENTED);
765
766 return ((rdataset->methods->addglue)(rdataset, version, msg));
767}
